---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="IEDC Fund Updates.">
  <section class="leap-wrapper relative">
    <div
      class="relative leap-bg p-10 h-[500px] flex justify-center items-center flex-col"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-center font-semibold text-white text-lg md:text-2xl mb-3 relative"
      >
        <span class="text-9xl font-bold">S A L T</span><br />Startup Awareness
        and Leadership Training
      </h1>
      <hr class="w-[4%] h-[4px] bg-[#00BABE] mx-auto mb-5 border-none" />
    </div>

    <div class="about-salt mt-9 md:mt-7  relative leading-8 bg-[#e4e4e4]">
      <div class="md:w-2/3 p-6 md:p-11 my-auto mx-auto text-justify">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          <span class="overline decoration-[#004C9F] decoration-[3px]">Ab</span
          >out the Project
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Startup Awareness and Leadership Training is a training program
          specifically designed for students of 9th & 11th standards. The SALT
          program will be conducted every Friday and Saturday for three weeks.
          IEDCs can select a nearby high school to implement this program, while
          the resources could be provided by the KSUM. The program aims to
          create awareness about entrepreneurship opportunities among school
          students and to inculcate a scientific spirit among young minds.
          Building an entrepreneurial mindset from an early stage is essential,
          as this is the stage where they can grasp a lot. This Program brings
          in an interesting teaching pedagogy that would be a perfect fit for
          the 21st century.
          <br /><br /><br />

          <div class="salt-sub md:flex bg-white shadow-md p-3 rounded-md">
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-6 md:border-r">
              <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">
                <span class="overline decoration-[#004C9F] decoration-[3px]"
                  >Ho</span
                >w to Apply
              </h1>
              <ul class="list-decimal px-4">
                <li>Nodal Officer shall log in to the Innovate Portal.</li>
                <li>Register for SALT under "Projects".</li>
                <li>
                  You may have to upload the names and contact details of the
                  students who will be taking the role of a resource person.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-6">
              <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">
                <span class="overline decoration-[#004C9F] decoration-[3px]"
                  >El</span
                >igibility
              </h1>
              <p>
                - Students from the 2nd year and above can apply for the post of
                the resource person.
                <br />
                 - (Batch 1 Application Closed) - <b>Implementing IEDC List</b>
                <br />
                 - Batch 2 - Application is <b>Now Open</b> in Innovate Portal
                under Projects - <b>Last Date is 15 July 2022.</b>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- <div class="salt-img md:w-1/3 hidden md:block">
        <img src="3d-rocket.png" class="h-screen w-auto mx-auto" alt="" />
      </div> -->
    </div>
    <div class=" salt-updates md:flex bg-white   rounded-b-md">
      

      <div
        class=" bg-white rounded-md shadow-lg shadow-slate-300 m-3 leading-7 my-auto md:flex"
      >
      <div class="salt-img md:w-1/3 hidden md:block">
        <img src="meeting.jpg" class="h-full  w-auto  mx-auto rounded-l-md" alt="" />
      </div>
        <div class="p-9 md:w-1/2">
          <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">Batch 1 Updates</h1>
           Kerala Startup Mission in collaboration with IEDC Trinity College of
          Engineering under the leadership of Dr. Arun Surendran, Strategic
          Director and Principal of Trinity College of Engineering, Trivandrum
          for 34 IEDCs.
          <br />
           The IEDCs will now identify Schools in the nearby vicinity and
          implement the SALT Programme specifically designed for students of 9th
          & 11th standards where selected trained IEDC Core Innovators from
          IEDCs will be offering training to the school students on Innovation &
          Entrepreneurship.
          <br /><br />

           The <b>First phase</b> of the SALT programme was conducted where
          trainers from IEDC Trinity College gave the innovators inputs on the
          modules.
          <br /><br />

           The <b>Second phase</b> is to identify Schools and Implement the
          Programme.
          <br /><br />
          <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">Timeline of Batch 1</h1>
          <p>
            The Mentoring session of <b>SALT Program</b> - 18th December,
            Saturday at Kerala Science & Technology Museum and Priyadarshini
            Planetarium, Trivandrum
            <br /><br />
             The Nodal Officer Implementation Meeting - 28th Dec 2021 (Virtual)
            <br /><br />
             The Nodal Officer Orientation & SALT Update Meeting - <b
              >8th Jan 2022 (Virtual)</b
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="salt-inst my-10">
      <img class="mx-auto" src="salt-img.png" alt="" />
      <h2 class="text-lg my-4 text-center font-semibold">
        SALT Batch 1: Institution wise Program Implementation Status
      </h2>

      <br />

      <div class="md:flex gap-3 justify-center items-center mb-14 p-4">
        <Card title="List of Salt Implementing Institutions" href="#" />
        <Card title="Playbook for Trainers" href="#" />
        <Card title="SALT Presentation" href="#" />
        <Card title="Playbook for IEDC" href="#" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

